#: ../../../cmds/fish_greeting.rst:2
msgid "fish_greeting - display a welcome message in interactive shells"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_greeting.rst:5
msgid "Synopsis"
msgstr "概要"

#: ../../../cmds/fish_greeting.rst:7
msgid "fish_greeting"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_greeting.rst:13
msgid ""
"function fish_greeting\n"
"    ...\n"
"end"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_greeting.rst:19
msgid "Description"
msgstr "描述"

#: ../../../cmds/fish_greeting.rst:21
msgid ""
"When an interactive fish starts, it executes fish_greeting and displays its "
"output."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_greeting.rst:23
msgid ""
"The default fish_greeting is a function that prints a variable of the same "
"name (``$fish_greeting``), so you can also just change that if you just want "
"to change the text."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_greeting.rst:25
msgid ""
"If :envvar:`SHELL_WELCOME` is set, it is displayed after the greeting. This "
"is a standard environment variable that may be set by tools like systemd's "
"``run0`` to display session information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_greeting.rst:27
msgid ""
"While you could also just put ``echo`` calls into config.fish, fish_greeting "
"takes care of only being used in interactive shells, so it won't be used e."
"g. with ``scp`` (which executes a shell), which prevents some errors."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_greeting.rst:30
msgid "Example"
msgstr "範例"

#: ../../../cmds/fish_greeting.rst:32
msgid "To just empty the text, with the default greeting function::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_greeting.rst:34
msgid "set -U fish_greeting"
msgstr "set -U fish_greeting"

#: ../../../cmds/fish_greeting.rst:36
msgid "or ``set -g fish_greeting`` in :ref:`config.fish <configuration>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_greeting.rst:38
msgid "A simple greeting:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_greeting.rst:42
msgid ""
"function fish_greeting\n"
"    echo Hello friend!\n"
"    echo The time is (set_color yellow)(date +%T)(set_color --reset) and "
"this machine is called $hostname\n"
"end"
msgstr ""
